CAUTION: This email originated from outside of NASA.  Please take care when clicking links or opening attachments.  Use the "Report Message" button to report suspicious messages to the NASA SOC. 


Dear Tim, James and Elizabeth,

 

On behalf of Professor Emma Sparkes, Rector of the University of New South Wales Canberra Australia, we are pleased to make a request for observer membership of the IAWN.

Find enclosed a cover letter from Professor Sparkes and a signed statement of intent.

 

UNSW Canberra in partnership with CSIRO, JPL, University of Western Australia and University of Tasmania is continuing the development of an asteroid monitoring capability from Australia and we feel the work of our staff and students will contribute to the IAWN. 

Our proposition is to establish an initial and coordinated Australian University presence at the IAWN, learning of and contributing asteroid science, where we are able.

 

Thank you for your kind consideration.

 

Best wishes,

 

Ed Kruzins

Professor UNSW Canberra Space

Northcott Drive

Campbell, ACT

 

 


